values:
That is what I have been asking myself for the past couple of days.&nbsp; 

As you walk down&nbsp;Rue de Jean Medecin&nbsp;&amp; through Place Messena they are everywhere and very well dressed I&nbsp;might&nbsp;add. But why do all the homeless people have, and Im so not kidding, puppies &amp; bunnies?!?!?! Sometimes both!&nbsp;Maybe they think that the cute animals will help them get more cash? But then how do they afford the food and carriers to keep them eating while on display? Aroo? If you could see me right now, you wouuld probably see a question mark over my head.&nbsp; 

Lets see, where did I leave off?&nbsp; 

Oh yes... Yesterday after having breakfast (yummy croissants!) and posting my previous entry, I ventured out to find the highest point in the city to get a great view. Well, that didnt quite work out... I went in the direction of the hill and got side-tracked somehow and ended up walking alllllll the way around the bottom of the hill. It was hot and sunny, so by the time I got to the steps that I would have had to climb, my feet were like - OH HELL NO!!! lol. It took a looong time to get there. Not that it wasnt worth it. I adore seeing the side streets and such, to me that is where the charm of most cities lies, especially in France. So I got some lovely snapshots, which I will post when I can get my damn laptop to work, hopefully somewhere in &lt;Rome!! Maybe not...&nbsp; 

So I walked by the beach and went to Cours Saleya which is the famous marketplace filled with fresh flowers, fruit, various food stuffs and art. I loved it there. I stopped by one of the fruit vendors and got the biggest nectarines I have ever seen (and the cheapest) and the most delicious. OMG it was like taking a bite of heaven! So, I continued to wander around and decided that I wanted to visit Eze. 

Eze is a medeival village not far from Nice. It is situated on a hill. I took the bus to the village and tried my dandest not to pass out from the clibing. lol. My back was throwing a fit like&nbsp;a 2 year old toddler, demanding attention, but I ignored it. If I didnt, I would be in a world of pain, and I cant give over to that right now, too much to do an see! So, I climbed and wandered my way through the beautiful streets of Eze. The streets are more like pathways, and in every nook and cranny there are tiny stores and cafes to stop and peek in or enjoy something yummilicious while trying to recover from the steps and hills around every corner. There were people finding little shaded spots and picnicing everywhere. That is one of my favorite things about France, there is always somewhere to stop and picnic and enjoy your tme there. ;) I took tons of pictures. Let me tell you how tiny the streets are, the vendors and hotels and people there have to pile everything onto carts and such to try an trek their way through the streets. It is a sight to see, I assure you. There is no way to get a car or anykind of truck up there.&nbsp; 

I found some shade,&nbsp;stopped, had a croissant that I stole from, breakfast (yay for being thrifty!) and had my heavenly nectarine. Seeing what time it was and noticing that the bus schedule was a little odd, I figured I would catch the bus then rather than being stranded there for 2 more hours. I was getting a little tired anyway. I JUST caught the bus after running down the street - lol. It was amusing. And I headed back to my hotel. Thank god for public transportation! The buses and trams here are fantastic and run until very late at night. They arent expensive and are pretty easy to navigate, as long as you have a fairly good sense of direction... which lucky for me, I do... I think. ;) Well, I do most of the time!&nbsp; 

A LITTLE NOTE TO THE ROE - As the bus was driving back towards Nice? I saw a hotel that we all have to stay at some day!! It was called, "La Fiancee du Pirate". The fiancee of the pirate. LOL! I thought of all of you. *wink* 

I got back to my hotel and crashed. Have I mentioned how hot it is here? I really hate the heat. I am a 75 degrees and under kind of girl. But it is bearable by the ocean. The breeze is sooooo nice. Plus, with the view, you coudnt possibly be anything but content and relaxed.&nbsp; 

Speaking of being relaxed, I sat there and asked myself why I was killing myself to get places when I should be resting before the hellacious schedule I will be having over the next few weeks. So I decided to skip my trips to Monaco and Cannes and take it easy. I needed to rest. 

With that in mind, I went to the beach. There are these beautiful spots on the promenade that are covered and provide shade about halfway down the coast. By the time you get there, they are much needed. But they have these lovely little benches that are under cover and just outside of the cover, so I sat down, took out my book and soaked in the sun for a bit. It was so beautiful. I absolutely loved it. I ended up just sitting there reading and watching the world go by for a few hours until it started to get dark. 

I heard that the nightlife is the most fun around Cours Saleya so I went back to the hotel, got dolled up and went back out as the sun was setting. Every cafe was abuzz with the crowds of hundreds of people having dinner or a drink. It was a gorgeous evening and I found a little cafe to just sit down and have a drink and take in the surrounding restaurants and cafes and all of the people. I really enjoyed it. ;) Before I went back to the hotel to get some much needed sleep, I went back to the Promenade and walked up and down until I couldnt anymore. There were people on the beach until I was there at about 1000 pm. Beach Volleyball games and people at the hotel bars abounded.&nbsp; 

I love it here. Seriously, it is going to be so hard to leave!!!&nbsp;

So, today I slept in, figuring that I should since it was my last day to do so! I got up and went straight for the place I didnt have energy to go to yesterday. 300 stairs later, I found myself staring at the amazing view of La Cote Dazure. Wow. There were more stairs to climb qs the night before &gt;I noticed that not far from that spot there was a waterfall all lit up. I loooooooove waterfalls. If I could, I would take&nbsp;a whole year out of my life and visit waterfalls all over the world. And I dont count Niagara Falls, I mean Falls in more natural habitats. The waterfall was another couple of hundred stairs up and over. But so worth it. I wish I could describe how beautiful it was up there, but my words would hardly do it justice. It was wonderful to sit there and breathe in the air and get covered by mist when the wind changed. I had gotten some lunch from the market down the street from me and I picniced a little ways down from the falls. It was perfectly quiet and all you could hear were brids singing happily and the sound of the falls. I felt so at peace. That is rare for me! Not a person walked by for about 20 minutes, and considering how touristy it is here, that is pretty amazing.&nbsp;

I finished lunch, trekked my way down and walked down the promenade to my spot fron yesterday afternoon and took in some sun. I need to get&nbsp;a tan. Seriously, I am whiter than white, it is scary. lol!!&nbsp;I met some people from Boston while sitting there. They were robbed right out of their hotel room. But they left the door unlocked while in the pool, so they knew it was their own fault. I felt bad for them. They really werent too worried about it though. 

That is about it. It is currently about 400pm here and I am probably just going to go back to the beach and get some more sun. Ive been neglecting my music so after some packing tonight, I plan on going over my music. Or I may take it with me... I dunno! Hope everything is well for all of you!&nbsp;

I am flying out to Rome tomorrow morning, so this could be my last post for a few days. Im not sure what my internet access will be like out there. If that is the case, hugs n smooches and I will post again as soon as I can!!

MWAH!

OK, these damn European keyboards r hard as hell to use!! Why cant&nbsp;we all use the same keyboards?!?!

First of all, let&nbsp;me tell u that my first day was not good.

I arrived a little late to the airport and by the time I checked my baggage, the flight&nbsp;was boarding. Blah! I ran through security as fast as I could&nbsp;and ran to my gate. OK. Crisis averted!&nbsp;

The flight&nbsp;wasnt bad at all! Mostly comfy.&nbsp;Not totally full, so there&nbsp;was room to stretch. Turbulence was down to a minimum. But my spine totally hates me now. Apparently it doesnt like sitting for&nbsp;8 hours!! Not that I blame it at all!!&nbsp;

When I finally got off the plane we were in the middle of the airfield. Yup, weirdness. You get off the plane and then take a bus to the airport. It was hottel than the 5th level of hell. Literally! So, I have exactly 20 minutes to get to my connection to Nice. I ran through the airport, stopped to go through mini-customs, stopped to exchange some cash for Euros and got to the gate with time to spare. I boarded another bus and 20 min later, I was on the plane to Nice. I didnt have time to take pics of the airport so you can all see what I mean, but I will when I go back to Rome on Thursday.&nbsp;

I saw the French Alps while flying back to Nice. The peaks were peeking out of the clouds. ;) It was gorgeous. I got to Nice and came to discover that they lost my baggage! Nice!... I mean as in the word not the place. lol! I am so exhausted by now, all I wanna do is get to the hotel and rest for a minute. So I grabbed a cab sans luggage and headed into the city. My cabbie told me that losing luggage happens all of the time and that I would probably get it that afternoon. Which actually did make me feel better.

So, I get to the hotel. And it is lovely. On a an unbeaten path that it right off of a beaten path ) ha. And it isnt far from the beach. Yay! When I got there, they didnt have my room ready and I was told to come back in a few hours. Ok, so I will go check out the scene. They gave me a map and I went for a walk. It is quite lovely around here. And parts are not so lovely. But that is expected. I had tons of time to kill so I found a schmancier part of town and went shopping. No, I didnt buy anything. I was being very good and I am on a really tight budget. But I definitely lusted after a few items. Like Bulgari sunglasses. drool. I am so shallow lol!

I went bck to my hotel and got my room. Yay! I took out my laptop n realized that I cannot use it w/out my power chord and where was that power chord? In my suitcase! Yah, I was having one hell of a day! So I called my mom from the hotel which will cost me an arm and a leg, because my calling card didnt work. At this point I just wanted to pass out from heat exhaustion cuz it is hotter than hell here!!! I left a message for my mom to tell her that I was here n ok n then went to explore somemore.&nbsp;

The beach is gorgeous!!! It was worth the trip just to see it. I took my time walking up and down the Promenade des Anglais which reminds me of CALIFORNIA with its palm trees and such. It was gorgeous. And I did a little more exploring. I really like it here.&nbsp;

I was starting to fade so I hiked back to my hotel, called my mom and then called the airport. They had my luggage and aouuld deliver it later on that night. REJOICE!!! lol. So I fell asleep and was woken when my luggage arrived. I got my stuff out and plugged in my laptop, which will not connect t the internet. sigh...

At that point I was done and decided just to go to sleep. Hopefully today will be better.

I am off to look at the gorgeous view from the highest point and then to the village of Eze and probably Monte Carlo. That is if the heat doesnt kill me first. Yuck!!

The Lakes Region Opera Idol Competition was great!

I was so freaked because one of my arias was just not up to par,&nbsp;and I KNEW that they would ask for it, because it is in german and they always ask for the damn german!&nbsp;The sheet&nbsp;that they sent&nbsp;originally said that they would choose the first piece, but when I got there, they said that I was allowed to choose - YAY! So of COURSE I did the&nbsp;piece that I could sing&nbsp;upside down, sideways and diagonally and be so sick that I want to die and still rock it - lol. It is "Il vecchiotto cerca moglie" Bertha's aria from Barber of Seville - It went very well.&nbsp;All of the judges got a good chuckle out of it! YAY! I loooove getting reactions, I really find that it helps egg me on and do that much better.&nbsp;So they thanked me and I left. YAY! The only problem was that the accompanist TOTALLY messed up on the 2nd half. He lost his place and could not pick it back up, so I paused for the accompinament where I was supposed to, and when I didn't hear it, I continued. Totally unrattled. I was so proud of myself! It didn't phase me at all. The accompanist was like, you did a cut, and I couldn't follow. And I said, no I didn't. Which I didn't because I've been doing this aria for 2 years and we have NEVER cut anything out of it. It was he who messed up, not me. But whatever. Nothing I could do about it.

At work that afternoon I got a call saying that I was in the semi-finals! EEEE! I was sooooo shocked becuase I heard some of the other singers, and they were truly amazing. The Semis were the next day (Saturday the 3rd) and my time was late in the afternoon. There was a really awful Nor'Easter to drive through, that was not fun. But my mom and I made it. And OF COURSE they asked for the German piece first. (Prince orlofsky's aria from Die Fledermaus)&nbsp;BUT they only wanted the 1st verse, which is great cuz that is the one that I knew! EEEEEEEE! So once I did that, I was like the rest is nothin! They then asked me for "Must The Winter Come So Soon?" from Vanessa. Then they asked me for the 1st verse of the aria I sang the day before again. And again, they giggled and laughed and enjoyed it. Then they said "Ok Giliana, we will see you tomorrow" To which I said OK THANKS! And then they said "Giliana, you do realize that we are putting you in the final?" I said "No..." He said - we are! I said thank you! And they all laughed. It was very amusing. So that whole night I was kind of in a state of shock while trying to pick out gowns as the grand finals concert was the next day and is was a full formal affair.&nbsp;

The next day was the Grand Finals concert. There were 15 finalists which were narrowed down from 57 singers. Some were rom new York, you can imagine how shocked I was that I was in the same competition as them. They were very very talented. And most were really nice. Got to know some great people, including some fellow mezzos. :) I went first and they told me the night before that I would be singing my best aria which I did the first day. YAY! It sucks to go first, cuz you get kind of forgotten. But I was glad to get it over with. In the end, I won a contract with the Lakes Region Opera Company for a role in Suor Angelica. I didn't win first prize, but that doesn't matter.&nbsp;

I spoke with one of the judges and he told me that he hoped that I was ready to do that role a gazillion times (Bertha who is the maid in Barber of Seville) as I do it so well and will be doing it for the rest of my life. He said that I need to specialize and find roles such as those and there was no doubt in his mind that I will have no trouble getting continuous work from now on. He also says that he hears Wagner in my future. Right now I am far too young, but he says it is there. He said he loved how I could just take the stage and be larger than life and that my charisma was something that you just can't learn. I was soooo taken aback by all of this. He was very very very blunt with all of the other singers and said don't do this and don't do that to all of them. But to me, he was really nice, very blunt also, but had nothing but good things to say. It was so cool!&nbsp;

So, now I will be performing in Suor Angelica in June. We'll see what happens after that. :)

But here is a little singing update -&nbsp;

for those of you who don't know, I am singing in a competition&nbsp;this week.&nbsp;Say it with me now&nbsp;- AHHHHH!!!

I could really&nbsp;really really use some of your good vibage at about 12:00 noon on Friday as that is when I will be singing in the first round.&nbsp;

The second round (if&nbsp;I make it) will take place on Saturday evening and&nbsp;the final round is Sunday when there will be a Grand Finals Concert which will be broadcast live. EEK!

I will let you all know how it went and if I make it through to the second and final rounds. PRAY FOR ME!!!

Thanks everyone, I appreciate it!&nbsp;&nbsp;
